dim: the dimension of simplex we are searching for\n\nYields\n-------\nsimplices"]}], "variables": [{"name": "zen_mapper.komplex.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "zen_mapper.komplex.Simplex", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "zen_mapper.komplex.Simplex.__new__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "vertices", "type": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "collections.abc.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zen_mapper.komplex.Simplex.dim", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": {"name": "Self", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_extensions.Self", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["The dimension of the simplex\n\nThe dimension of a simplex is defined to be one less than the number of\nelements in the simplex. Thus a 0-simplex (a vertex) is comprised of a\nsingle point, a 1-simplex (an edge) is comprised of two points, and so\non."]}, {"name": "zen_mapper.komplex.Simplex.faces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": {"name": "Self", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_extensions.Self", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "collections.abc.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Self", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_extensions.Self", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["All the faces of a simplex\n\nA simplex \u03b8 is a face of \u03c4 if and only if \u03b8 \u2286 \u03c4. Note that as \u03c4 \u2286 \u03c4\nthat \u03c4 is a face of \u03c4!\n\nYields\n------\nsimplex\n    a face of the simplex"]}, {"name": "zen_mapper.komplex.Simplex.vertices", "asynchrono